msgSnippet: Without attempting to read each story, this looks fine to me Paul.  Many thanks. I not though that the second and subsequent page on some articles is headed
messageBody:
Without attempting to read each story, this looks fine to me Paul.  Many thanks.

I not though that the second and subsequent page on some articles is headed "contents" (as it is on the other feeds).  Is this intentional?

regards

Moira

 

On 30/11/2007, Paul Tremblay <phthenry@... > wrote:

I now have news from the BBC:

http://quikscript.sourceforge.net/qs_bbc_top_news.pdf

You will notice that the news stories don't appear as neat as the other
news. I spent both yesterday evening and this evening trying to work
with the mess of BBC, and this is the best I can do.

Paul
